metadata.name: Dusty Swan
metadata.description:
NGC 7000 & IC5067  
AUGUST 2022  
Besides the swans tail in the Cygnus constellation, lies a bright patch of ionized gas, NGC 7000 & IC 5067. This deep space object is most commonly known as the North American Nebula & The Pelican Nebula.  
This image was captured on a bortle 3-4 zone 40 minutes away from my hometown.

Technical Details  
45X60s Lights and calibration frames.  
ISO 800  
F:4

Equipment  
Camera: Canon 1300d (Ha Mod)  
Optic: Rokinon 135mm F2.0 lens.  
Tracking Mount: Sky Watcher Star Adventurer

Software  
Stacked in DSS  
Processed in Photoshop  
Starnet V2
